      "comment": "SPLASH OF PAYNT (2) has been racing in great heart at Redcliffe. Raced parked but stuck on to win three back and has been good as runner-up in both outings since, finishing just a head from the winner last time. Likely to get the favours from this nice draw. Leading hope. AMAMI (7) has been taking on standing start races of late but came from similar barriers to this to win the last two times he started behind a mobile so is better suited here. CHEZZ DALE NZ (10) may need a touch of luck from the back row but owns a good record at this circuit and distance. I OF THE HURRIKANE (1) draws much better than last start and placed from this barrier three back so is worth some thought.",
